2. Elements can only be added or removed from the top of the stack, also known as the "head".
3. The operations that can be performed on a stack are "push" (to add an element to the top of the stack) and "pop" (to remove the top element from the stack).
4. The "peek" operation can also be used to view the top element of the stack without removing it.
5. A stack can be implemented using an array or a linked list data structure.

